'''Soufiane Rahimi''' ({{langx|ar|سُفْيَان رَحِيمِيّ}}; born 2 June 1996) is a Moroccan professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[forward (association football)|forward]] for [[UAE Pro League]] club [[Al Ain FC|Al Ain]] and the [[Morocco national football team|Morocco national team]].

Rahimi started his professional career playing for [[Raja CA]], before being sent on a loan to [[Étoile de Casablanca]]. Rahimi then returned back to his former club after the end of his loan, helping the club win the [[2019–20 Botola]], the 2018 and 2021 [[CAF Confederation Cup]] and the [[2019–20 Arab Club Champions Cup]]. He then signed with [[UAE Pro League]] side [[Al Ain FC|Al-Ain]], where he led the club to win the [[2023–24 AFC Champions League]], finishing as the tournament's top scorer with 13 goals.

A full international for [[Morocco national football team|Morocco]] since 2021, Soufiane represented the nation at the [[2020 African Nations Championship]], [[2021 FIFA Arab Cup]] and [[2021 Africa Cup of Nations]]. Rahimi was the top goalscorer of the [[2020 African Nations Championship]], with five goals. At the [[Football at the 2024 Summer Olympics – Men's tournament|2024 Summer Olympics]], he was selected as one of the three overage players of [[Morocco national under-23 football team|Morocco Olympic]] and won a bronze medal, as well as the top scorer award.

== Club career ==
=== Raja Club Athletic ===
Rahimi scored a total of four goals for [[Raja CA]] in [[2018 CAF Confederation Cup]] campaign,<ref>[https://ghanasoccernet.com/confederation-cup-soufiane-rahimi-scores-twice-as-moroccos-raja-crush-vita-club-3-0-in-final-first-leg Confederation Cup: Soufiane Rahimi scores twice as Morocco's Raja crush Vita Club 3–0 in final first-leg] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181203152318/https://ghanasoccernet.com/confederation-cup-soufiane-rahimi-scores-twice-as-moroccos-raja-crush-vita-club-3-0-in-final-first-leg |date=3 December 2018 }}. ''GhanaSoccernet.com''.</ref> including two goals<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20181204005650/https://af.reuters.com/article/sportsNews/idAFKBN1O20KZ-OZASP Raja Casablanca win African Confederation Cup]. Reuters.</ref> in the [[2018 CAF Confederation Cup Final|final]] against [[AS Vita Club]] in [[Casablanca]]. This allowed them to qualify and play the [[2019 CAF Super Cup]] against [[Espérance Sportive de Tunis]]; which then ended up winning after a 2–1 victory.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Raja beat Esperance to win Super Cup |language=en-GB |work=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/47754856 |access-date=2022-02-27 |archive-date=27 February 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220227173858/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/47754856 |url-status=live }}</ref>

He has been one of the highest performing players in his last two seasons in [[Botola Pro|Botola]], becoming a top pick for the [[Morocco national football team|Moroccan national team]] coach to join the local squad. He has been closely linked with a move to Europe, and has stated his ambition of joining the [[Serie A]] in press conferences.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2021-06-03 |title=Soufiane Rahimi is interested in a Serie A club |url=https://moroccolatestnews.com/soufiane-rahimi-is-interested-in-a-serie-a-club/ |access-date=2022-02-27 |website=Morocco Latest News |language=en-US |archive-date=27 February 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220227173858/https://moroccolatestnews.com/soufiane-rahimi-is-interested-in-a-serie-a-club/ |url-status=usurped }}</ref>

=== Al Ain ===
On 21 August 2021, he had played his last match with Raja CA in the [[2020 Arab Club Champions Cup Final]], therefore defeating [[Al-Ittihad Club (Jeddah)|Al-Ittihad]] in penalties; before transferring to Emirati club [[Al Ain FC|Al Ain]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kingfut.com/2021/08/08/al-ahly-target-soufiane-rahimi-joins-emirati-side-al-ain/ |title=Al Ahly target Soufiane Rahimi joins Emirati side Al Ain |website=kingfut.com |date=8 August 2021 |access-date=23 August 2021 |archive-date=8 August 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210808223653/https://www.kingfut.com/2021/08/08/al-ahly-target-soufiane-rahimi-joins-emirati-side-al-ain/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On September 17, Rahimi scored his first goal for the club in a 4–1 victory against [[Al-Ittihad Kalba SC|Al-Ittihad Kalba]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=بالفيديو: رحيمي يسجل أول أهدافه بقميص العين الإماراتي |url=https://ar.le360.ma/sports/183424 |access-date=2022-02-27 |website=ar.le360.ma |language=ar |archive-date=27 February 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220227173900/https://ar.le360.ma/sports/183424 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2021-09-17 |title=رحيمي يسجل أول أهدافه مع العين ويقوده للفوز على اتحاد كلباء برباعية -فيديو |url=https://ar.lesiteinfo.com/sport/%D8%B1%D8%AD%D9%8A%D9%85%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D8%B3%D8%AC%D9%84-%D8%A3%D9%88%D9%84-%D8%A3%D9%87%D8%AF%D8%A7%D9%81%D9%87-%D9%85%D8%B9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D9%8A%D9%86-%D9%88%D9%8A%D9%82%D9%88%D8%AF%D9%87-%D9%84-566506.html |access-date=2022-02-27 |website=Le Site Info Arabe |language=ar |archive-date=27 February 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220227173859/https://ar.lesiteinfo.com/sport/%D8%B1%D8%AD%D9%8A%D9%85%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D8%B3%D8%AC%D9%84-%D8%A3%D9%88%D9%84-%D8%A3%D9%87%D8%AF%D8%A7%D9%81%D9%87-%D9%85%D8%B9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D9%8A%D9%86-%D9%88%D9%8A%D9%82%D9%88%D8%AF%D9%87-%D9%84-566506.html |url-status=live }}</ref> On 12 November 2022, Rahimi scored a double against [[Sharjah FC|Sharjah]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-11-12 |title=رحيمي يواصل التألق في الدوري الإماراتي |url=https://www.hespress.com/%D8%B1%D8%AD%D9%8A%D9%85%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%B5%D9%84-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AA%D8%A3%D9%84%D9%82-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AF%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A5%D9%85%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%AA-1076569.html |access-date=2022-11-15 |website=Hespress - هسبريس جريدة إلكترونية مغربية |language=ar |archive-date=15 November 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221115215410/https://www.hespress.com/%D8%B1%D8%AD%D9%8A%D9%85%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%B5%D9%84-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AA%D8%A3%D9%84%D9%82-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AF%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A5%D9%85%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%AA-1076569.html |url-status=live }}</ref> On 7 November 2023, Rahmi scored in a 3–2 victory against Al Fayha in the [[2023–24 AFC Champions League]] to qualify his team into the Knock-out stages.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Group A: Al Fayha (KSA) 2-3 Al Ain FC (UAE) |url=https://www.the-afc.com/en/club/afc_champions_league/news/group_a_al_fayha_ksa_v_al_ain_fc_uae_2.html |access-date=2023-11-07 |website=the-AFC |language=en |archive-date=7 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231107213732/https://www.the-afc.com/en/club/afc_champions_league/news/group_a_al_fayha_ksa_v_al_ain_fc_uae_2.html |url-status=live }}</ref> In the [[2023–24 AFC Champions League#Round of 16|Round of 16]], Rahimi scored the winning goal against [[FC Nasaf|Nasaf]] to qualify the team to the Quarter-finals.<ref>{{Cite web |title=AFC Champions League: Soufiane Rahimi nets late winner as Al Ain edge Nasaf |url=https://www.the-afc.com/en/club/afc_champions_league/news/rahimi_nets_late_winner_as_al_ain_edge_nasaf.html |access-date=2024-02-21 |website=the-AFC |language=en |archive-date=21 February 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240221204032/https://www.the-afc.com/en/club/afc_champions_league/news/rahimi_nets_late_winner_as_al_ain_edge_nasaf.html |url-status=live }}</ref> Rahimi went on to score the winning goal in a 1–0 victory against [[Al Nassr FC|Al Nassr]] in the first leg of the quarter-finals and two goals in the second leg.<ref>{{Cite web |title=AFC Champions League: Rahimi strike gives Al Ain advantage over Al Nassr |url=https://www.the-afc.com/en/club/afc_champions_league/news/rahimi_strike_gives_al_ain_advantage_over_al_nassr.html |access-date=2024-03-06 |website=the-AFC |language=en |archive-date=17 April 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240417181223/https://www.the-afc.com/en/club/afc_champions_league/news/rahimi_strike_gives_al_ain_advantage_over_al_nassr.html |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=MSN |url=https://www.msn.com/ |access-date=2024-03-11 |website=www.msn.com |archive-date=17 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231217233945/http://www.msn.com/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On 15 March 2023, Rahimi scored his first ever hat-trick for the club in a 4–0 win against [[Ajman Club|Ajman]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Al Ain Thrash Ajman 4-0 in ADNOC Pro League |url=https://www.uaeproleague.ae/en/news-and-gallery/al-ain-thrash-ajman-4-0-in-adnoc-pro-league |access-date=2024-03-15 |website=www.uaeproleague.ae |language=en |archive-date=15 March 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240315205453/https://www.uaeproleague.ae/en/news-and-gallery/al-ain-thrash-ajman-4-0-in-adnoc-pro-league |url-status=live }}</ref> In the first leg of the 2023–24 AFC Champions League Semi-final, Rahimi scored a hat-trick in a 4–2 victory against [[Al Hilal SFC]], putting an end to Al Hilal 34 game winning streak.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-04-17 |title=Al Ain ends Al Hilal's 34 game winning streak |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/story/_/id/39963232/al-hilals-record-34-game-winning-streak-snapped-al-ain |access-date=2024-04-23 |website=ESPN.com |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-04-17 |title=Al Hilal's record 34-match winning run ends at Al Ain |url=https://www.france24.com/en/live-news/20240417-al-hilal-s-record-34-match-winning-run-ends-at-al-ain |access-date=2024-04-23 |website=France 24 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=AFC Champions League Semi-final: Al Ain stun Al Hilal in classic |url=https://www.the-afc.com/en/club/afc_champions_league/news/al_ain_stun_al_hilal_in_classic.html |access-date=2024-04-23 |website=the-AFC |language=en}}</ref> In the [[2024 AFC Champions League final]], Al Ain won 6–3 in aggregate against [[Yokohama F. Marinos]], with Rahimi scoring a brace in the second leg, and winning the Most Valuable Player and Top scorer awards.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |title=AFC Champions League - Al Ain's Rahimi wins MVP, Top Scorer awards |url=https://www.the-afc.com/en/club/afc_champions_league/news/al_ains_rahimi_wins_mvp_top_scorer_awards.html |access-date=2024-05-26 |website=the-AFC |language=en}}</ref>

On 24 October 2024, Rahimi along with his international teammate [[Achraf Hakimi]], were nominated for the [[African Footballer of the Year|2024 African Footballer of the Year award]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=MASAITI |first=Amira EL |date=2024-10-24 |title=Moroccans Hakimi and Rahimi Nominated for CAF Player of the Year Award |url=https://en.hespress.com/94035-moroccans-hakimi-and-rahimi-nominated-for-caf-player-of-the-year-award.html |access-date=2024-11-04 |website=HESPRESS English - Morocco News |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=CAF announces #CAFAwards24 Nominees for Men's Categories |url=https://www.cafonline.com/news/caf-announces-cafawards24-nominees-for-men-s-categories/ |access-date=2024-11-04 |website=CAF announces #CAFAwards24 Nominees for Men’s Categories |language=en-GB}}</ref>

==International career ==
In 2018, Rahimi was called up to the [[Morocco A' national football team|Moroccan national A' team]] by [[Jamal Sellami]].<ref>[http://sport.le360.ma/football/video-soufiane-rahimi-au-nom-du-pere-63007 Soufiane Rahimi, au nom du père] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181204200621/http://sport.le360.ma/football/video-soufiane-rahimi-au-nom-du-pere-63007 |date=4 December 2018 }}. ''Le360.ma''.</ref> Rahimi represented Morocco in the [[2020 African Nations Championship]], He scored a double in his third game of the group stages against [[Uganda national football team|Uganda]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Football |first=CAF-Confedération Africaine du |title=Holders Morocco reach CHAN quarters, Uganda out |url=https://www.cafonline.com/total-african-nations-championship/news/holders-morocco-reach-chan-quarters-uganda-out |access-date=2022-02-28 |website=CAFOnline.com |language=en |archive-date=28 February 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220228110057/https://www.cafonline.com/total-african-nations-championship/news/holders-morocco-reach-chan-quarters-uganda-out |url-status=live }}</ref> He scored in the quarter-finals in a 3–1 victory against [[Zambia national football team|Zambia]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Football |first=CAF-Confedération Africaine du |title=Defending champions Morocco see off Zambia to reach CHAN semis |url=https://www.cafonline.com/total-african-nations-championship/news/defending-champions-morocco-see-off-zambia-to-reach-chan-semis |access-date=2022-02-28 |website=CAFOnline.com |language=en |archive-date=25 December 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211225110216/https://www.cafonline.com/total-african-nations-championship/news/defending-champions-morocco-see-off-zambia-to-reach-chan-semis |url-status=live }}</ref> Morocco won an astonishing 4–0 in the semi-finals against [[Cameroon national football team|Cameroon]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Football |first=CAF-Confedération Africaine du |title=Two-goal hero Rahimi sends Morocco to CHAN final, Cameroon crash out |url=https://www.cafonline.com/total-african-nations-championship/news/two-goal-hero-rahimi-sends-morocco-to-chan-final-cameroon-crash-out |access-date=2022-02-28 |website=CAFOnline.com |language=en |archive-date=28 February 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220228110056/https://www.cafonline.com/total-african-nations-championship/news/two-goal-hero-rahimi-sends-morocco-to-chan-final-cameroon-crash-out |url-status=live }}</ref> With this performance, Rahimi managed of scoring a total of five goals thus helping his country to achieve the title and becoming the first and only country to win the Championship back to back. He was awarded top scorer and best player of the tournament.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Football|first=CAF-Confedération Africaine du|title=Morocco star Rahimi wins CHAN best player, top-scorer awards|url=https://www.cafonline.com/total-african-nations-championship/news/soufiane-rahimi-best-player-of-total-chan-cameroon-2020|access-date=30 December 2021|website=CAFOnline.com|language=en|archive-date=7 December 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221207140236/https://www.cafonline.com/total-african-nations-championship/news/soufiane-rahimi-best-player-of-total-chan-cameroon-2020|url-status=live}}</ref>

Over two years after his last appearances with the national team, Rahimi was included in Morocco's squad for the friendlies against [[Angola national football team|Angola]] and [[Mauritania national football team|Mauritania]] in March 2024.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Yabiladi.com |title=Morocco squad announcement : Brahim Diaz, Soufiane Rahimi to play against Angola, Mauritania |url=https://en.yabiladi.com/articles/details/147665/morocco-squad-announcement-brahim-diaz.html |access-date=2024-03-15 |website=en.yabiladi.com |language=en |archive-date=15 March 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240315000705/https://en.yabiladi.com/articles/details/147665/morocco-squad-announcement-brahim-diaz.html |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Simpara |first=Mahamadou |title=Regragui Calls Up All Star Lineup for Upcoming Friendlies |url=https://www.moroccoworldnews.com/2024/03/361377/regragui-calls-up-all-star-lineup-for-upcoming-friendlies |access-date=2024-03-15 |website=Morocco World News |language=en |archive-date=15 March 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240315000704/https://www.moroccoworldnews.com/2024/03/361377/regragui-calls-up-all-star-lineup-for-upcoming-friendlies |url-status=live }}</ref> He came off the bench against Angola and helped create the own-goal by [[David Carmo]]. Morocco won 1–0.<ref>{{Cite web |last=d'Agadir-Friendlies 1 |first=Stade |title=Morocco vs Angola |url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-us/soccer/friendlies/morocco-vs-angola-2024-03-22 |access-date=2024-03-23 |website=beIN SPORTS |language=en-us |archive-date=23 March 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240323015924/https://www.beinsports.com/en-us/soccer/friendlies/morocco-vs-angola-2024-03-22 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Rahhou |first=Jihane |title=Morocco Claims 1-0 Victory over Angola in Friendly Match |url=https://www.moroccoworldnews.com/2024/03/361563/morocco-claims-1-0-victory-over-angola-in-friendly-match |access-date=2024-03-23 |website=Morocco World News |language=en |archive-date=23 March 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240323015924/https://www.moroccoworldnews.com/2024/03/361563/morocco-claims-1-0-victory-over-angola-in-friendly-match |url-status=live }}</ref>

Rahimi was selected for Morocco's squad to compete in the [[Football at the 2024 Summer Olympics – Men's tournament|men's football]] at the [[2024 Summer Olympics]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=MASAITI |first=Amira EL |date=2024-07-04 |title=Morocco's Head Coach unveils squad list for 2024 Olympic Games |url=https://en.hespress.com/87471-moroccos-head-coach-unveils-squad-list-for-2024-olympic-games.html |access-date=2024-07-18 |website=HESPRESS English - Morocco News |language=en-US}}</ref> In the opening match of the group stage, Rahimi scored a brace in a 2–1 victory against [[Argentina national under-23 football team|Argentina]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-07-24 |title=Fan invasion chaos mars Morocco win vs Argentina |url=https://www.espn.com/olympics/story/_/id/40631533/morocco-beat-argentina-amid-fan-invasion-chaos |access-date=2024-07-24 |website=ESPN.com |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-07-24 |title=Olympics football: Crowd trouble sees Morocco's win over Argentina delayed before play resumes |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/articles/cv2gzll8wn5o |access-date=2024-07-24 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> He then scored a goal in a 2–1 defeat against [[Ukraine Olympic football team|Ukraine]] and a goal in a 3–0 victory against [[Iraq Olympic football team|Iraq]],<ref>{{Cite web |last=MASAITI |first=Amira EL |date=2024-07-27 |title=Morocco loses to Ukraine 2-1 in second Olympics football match |url=https://en.hespress.com/88642-morocco-loses-to-ukraine-2-1-in-second-olympics-match.html |access-date=2024-07-31 |website=HESPRESS English - Morocco News |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=MASAITI |first=Amira EL |date=2024-07-30 |title=Morocco beats Iraq 3-0 in last Olympics group stage game, qualifying for quarterfinals |url=https://en.hespress.com/88842-morocco-beats-iraq-3-0-in-last-olympics-group-stage-game-qualifying-for-next-round.html |access-date=2024-07-31 |website=HESPRESS English - Morocco News |language=en-US}}</ref> thus surpassing [[Ahmed Faras]] and becoming the top Moroccan goalscorer for the [[Football at the Summer Olympics|Summer Olympics]] with four goals.<ref>{{Cite web |last=MASAITI |first=Amira EL |date=2024-07-30 |title=Rahimi breaks Moroccan football Olympic record |url=https://en.hespress.com/88848-rahimi-breaks-moroccan-football-olympic-record.html |access-date=2024-07-31 |website=HESPRESS English - Morocco News |language=en-US}}</ref> Rahimi ended the Olympics scoring a total of 8 goals in 6 appearances, becoming the first player to score in all 6 games of a single Olympic edition.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-08-08 |title=Morocco forward Soufiane Rahimi sets Olympic scoring record 🇲🇦 |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/morocco-forward-soufiane-rahimi-sets-olympic-scoring-record-39867227 |access-date=2024-08-08 |website=OneFootball |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Daoudi |first=Asmae |title=Sofiane Rahimi Joins Morocco's Olympic Legends with Record-Breaking Performance |url=https://moroccoworldnews.com/2024/08/364335/sofiane-rahimi-joins-moroccos-olympic-legends-with-record-breaking-performance |access-date=2024-08-08 |website=Morocco World News |language=en}}</ref>

On 11 December 2025, Rahimi was called up to the Morocco squad for the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cafonline.com/afcon2025/news/morocco-name-star-studded-afcon-squad-as-hakimi-makes-cut-but-diop-misses-out/|title=Morocco name star-studded AFCON squad as Hakimi makes cut but Diop misses out|publisher=[[Confederation of African Football]]|date=11 December 2025|access-date=12 December 2025}}</ref>

== Personal life ==
Born in [[Casablanca]], Soufiane Rahimi is the older brother of [[Houssine Rahimi]], who is also a footballer.{{citation needed|date=May 2025}}

